That sounds like a good approach in H1.

FYI in H3, Crawl-Delay is honored separately from the top-level &#39;ignore&#39; 
setting.

That is, the directives are always read and remembered, and the top 
level coarse &#39;honor&#39;/&#39;ignore&#39; setting only refers to the URI 
disallow/allow decisions, made by the PreconditionEnforcer module.

Crawl-Delay is consulted by the later, rate-hinting DispositionProcessor 
module, and will be respected up to value of the 
&#39;respectCrawlDelayUpToSeconds&#39; parameter. (Longer crawl-delays will be 
truncated to that parameter. So if you needed to ignore Crawl-Delay, you 
could set that value to 0.)

- Gordon

